Title: Simple To-Do List Management Program

Description:
This C++ program is a simple to-do list management system that allows users to add tasks, view tasks, and delete tasks from a list. It provides a menu-driven interface for easy interaction.

Features:

Add A New Task: Users can add new tasks to the to-do list. The program ensures that the task list does not exceed the maximum capacity.
View The Tasks: Users can view all the tasks currently present in the list.
Delete Task: Users can delete a specific task from the list by entering its corresponding index.
Instructions for Use:

Compilation: Compile the program using a C++ compiler. For example, you can use g++ on Unix-like systems or MinGW on Windows.

Copy code
g++ -o todo_list todo_list.cpp
Execution: Run the compiled executable.

bash
Copy code
./todo_list
Menu Navigation: Follow the on-screen menu to perform desired operations.

Enter 1 to add a new task.
Enter 2 to view the tasks.
Enter 3 to delete a task.
Enter 0 to end the program.
Dependencies:

This program utilizes the iostream and string libraries from the C++ Standard Library.
Additional Notes:

The program ensures robust input handling and includes necessary error messages for invalid user input.
It clears the input buffer appropriately to prevent unexpected behavior.
The task list has a maximum capacity of 10 tasks, ensuring memory efficiency.
Deleting a task adjusts the task count accordingly, maintaining the integrity of the task list.
